Re:  Unauthorized Use of Intellectual Property  
 
Dear Designated Agent: 
 
  
 
This letter is to provide you notice pursuant to 17 U.S.C. § 512 (c)(3)(A) of
unauthorized use of copyrighted material of Proficient Audio Systems ("Proficient"),
a division of SpeakerCraft, Inc. (such copyrighted material is referred to as
"Proficient") by your client, grouptarget.com, at the URL www.grouptarget.com.
Proficient has a good faith belief that use of the Infringing Material by your
client is not authorized by Proficient, its agents, or the law, and the information
contained in this letter is accurate.   
 
  
 
The specific works, graphics or other material Proficient believes to be infringed
or to be the subject of infringing activity (the "Infringing Material") are
copyrighted images from Proficient's website.  Specific violations of copyrighted
images by www.grouptarget.com are listed below this paragraph. 
 
  
 
http://www.grouptarget.com/Viewer.jsp?qid=1005627 
 
  
 
There are various additional locations of infringement on www.grouptarget.com
website.  The above list is a specific sample of some of these, but all
infringements need to be addressed. 
 
  
 
Therefore, pursuant to the requirements of 17 U.S.C. § 512(c)(1)(C), Proficient
hereby demands that you remove or disable access to the Infringing Material in an
expeditious manner.   
 
  
 
If you have questions, please contact Net Enforcers Compliance Management Department
via facsimile to 352-505-0040, or via email to
Compliance.Management@NetEnforcers.com.  All communication must be in writing. Net
Enforcers is authorized to handle and resolve this matter with you and has already
been involved with this case.  Calls directly to Proficient will not be accepted. 
If your designated agent or representation does not respond to this demand as
requested by 5:00 p.m. on 10/19/2006, we will assume that this demand has been
rejected and we will proceed accordingly. 
 
  
 
Sincerely, 
 
VCLM law 
 
  
 
Lance C. Venable 
 
Attorney at Law 
 
  
 
